# Styling

Dual system — both are intentional:

| Use for | Where |
|---------|--------|
| Blocks, carousels, header/nav chrome | Nested SCSS in `src/app/css/scss/main.scss` |
| Page layout, spacing, simple grids | Tailwind utility classes in JSX |
| Brand colors / type scale | CSS variables in `globals.css` (`--s-accent`, `--f-h1`, `--f-h2`, …) |

## Rules

- New block UI styles go in `main.scss` (do not create a parallel SCSS architecture or CSS Modules unless asked)
- Prefer `var(--s-accent)` / `var(--f-h*)` over hardcoding brand colors
- Preserve CMS-injected GreenShift CSS (`greenshiftInlineCss`, global styles from `getGlobalStyle()`)
- Fonts: DBHeavent (body), DinPro (`.font-brand`) — do not swap to Inter/system stacks
- Sass include path is configured in `next.config.mjs` (`./src/app/css/scss`)
- `_fonts.scss` exists but is not imported; fonts typically come from WP global CSS — do not “fix” by inventing new font loading without checking

```scss
// ✅ Block styles live nested in main.scss
.retail-information-popover {
  // ...
}
```
